        "text": "Now, we can't be sure this means they're [blank], but since the [blank] of other parts of the body didn't change, it does suggest that something was going on. And Snell-Rood thinks that this change might [blank] the cognitive demands of adjusting to city life - having to look in different places to find [blank], for example, and a whole [blank] of new dangers.",
        "blanks": [{ "answer": "more intelligent" }, { "answer": "sizes" }, { "answer": "reflect" }, { "answer": "food" }, { "answer": "set" }],
